author: Steph Cockroft For Mailonline
title: Workmen prepare site ahead of search for Corrie McKeague | Daily Mail Online
text: Search teams hunting for missing RAF airman Corrie McKeague begin to clear away 8,000 tons of rubbish from a landfill where his body is believed to be Workmen in hi-vis jackets and helmets are currently at the tip in Milton, Cambs Site is where lorry deposited waste from bins close to where Corrie was last seen Mr McKeague, 23, was seen on CCTV walking down dead end full of rubbish bins Police say search of the 1,100 sq ft site is expected to take at least eight weeks
